The paper deals with algorithms for constructing planar graphs with certain properties, which is a topic in computational geometry (cs.CG). The use of the Delaunay triangulation and the approximation scheme for the traveling salesperson problem suggest that the paper may also be relevant to the sub-categories of data structures (cs.DS) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The mention of weight and minimum spanning tree suggest that numerical analysis (cs.NA) may also be relevant. Finally, the use of approximation algorithms suggests that artificial intelligence (cs.AI) may also be a relevant sub-category.
